      • pKapKbMolecule

        public static double[] pKapKbMolecule(Molecule molecule)
                               throws PluginException
        Gets the smallest pKa and largest pKb of a molecule. The molecule is modified; clone it before sending it here.
        Parameters:
        molecule - a molecule
        Returns:
        an array in which the first value is the smallest pKa, and the second is the largest pKb (defined as the pKa of the conjugate acid)
        Throws:
        PluginException - when the plugin can't calculate the pKa

      • pKapKbMolecule

        public static double[] pKapKbMolecule(Molecule molecule,
                                      int stageIndex)
                               throws PluginException
        Gets the smallest pKa and largest pKb of a molecule. The molecule is modified; clone it before sending it here.
        Parameters:
        molecule - a molecule
        stageIndex - if molecule is part of a mechanism, index of the stage to which it belongs; provided just for the log
        Returns:
        an array in which the first value is the smallest pKa, and the second is the largest pKb (defined as the pKa of the conjugate acid)
        Throws:
        PluginException - when the plugin can't calculate the pKa

      • pKapKbAtoms

        public static double[][] pKapKbAtoms(Molecule molecule)
                              throws PluginException
        Gets the pKa and pKb of each atom in a molecule. The molecule is modified; clone it before sending it here.
        Parameters:
        molecule - a molecule
        Returns:
        an array of arrays; first dimension is the atom index; in second dimension, first value is the smallest pKa, and the second is the largest pKb (defined as the pKa of the conjugate acid)
        Throws:
        PluginException - when the plugin can't calculate the pKa

      • pKapKbAtoms

        public static double[][] pKapKbAtoms(Molecule origMol,
                                     int stageIndex)
                              throws PluginException
        Gets the pKa and pKb of each atom in a molecule. The molecule is modified; clone it before sending it here.
        Parameters:
        origMol - a molecule
        stageIndex - if molecule is part of a mechanism, index of the stage to which it belongs; provided just for the log
        Returns:
        an array of arrays; first dimension is the atom index; in second dimension, first value is the smallest pKa, and the second is the largest pKb (defined as the pKa of the conjugate acid)
        Throws:
        PluginException - when the plugin can't calculate the pKa

      • getCpK

        private static double getCpK(Molecule mol,
                             int atmIndex)
        Guesses pKa of a C atom that JChem doesn't calculate. Assumes calling method has already checked that atom is C and bears H. Doesn't look for carbonyls, etc. because JChem already checks for those.
        Parameters:
        mol - a molecule
        atmIndex - C atom whose pKa to guess
        Returns:
        a pKa value for the C atom

      • specialCasePKs

        private static double[][] specialCasePKs(Molecule molecule)
        Gets the smallest pKa and largest pKb of molecules that JChem miscalculates. Values come from http://daecr1.harvard.edu/pdf/evans_pKa_table.pdf.
        Parameters:
        molecule - a molecule
        Returns:
        pKa and pKb values of each atom if it's a special case, null otherwise
